<td width="481" class="pageName">


Local Churches
</td>		
</tr>		

<tr>          
<td class="bodyText">
<p>

<br> 
There are number of churches that you can attend. Some churches are located on campus if you are not interested in making the trek. There are churches that are primarily one culture if you are more comfortable in that setting. Otherwise, check them out for yourself and decide which if right for you. Here are a couple of churches SCFers have attended/ are currently attending.:w


<br><br>

</p>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Antioch of Calvary Chapel
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is located in University City, and has an ethnically and
culturally diverse congregation. The Sunday services are
contemporary and the main emphasis is on teaching from the
Bible.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Stephanie Appiah ’10 (sappiah1)
<br />
<a href="www.antiochphilly.org">www.antiochphilly.org</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Blue Route Vineyard
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is a nearby non-denominational church with a large collage-age
population, predominately Caucasian but seeking to diversify.
The service is primarily musical worship and an engaging, biblically-based sermon.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Jeff Weaver ’10 (jweaver1) or Mi Zheng ’11 (mzheng1)
<br />
<a href="www.blueroutevineyard.com">www.blueroutevineyard.com</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>


<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Catholic Mass at Swarthmore
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is conveniently located right on campus, Sundays (10 am) and Wednesdays (12:30pm) in Bond Hall. Father Ed, the Catholic student advisor, delivers relevant and intelligent sermons aimed at Swarthmore students.<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Erik Smith ’10 (esmith4) or Cecelia Osowski ’10 (cosowsk1)
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Swarthmore Presbyterian Church 
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is located right next to the Palmer/Pittenger/Roberts dorms on Harvard Ave. Its congregation is fairly large with many families, and sermons are Bible-based.
<br />
<a href="www.swarthmorepres.org">www.swarthmorepres.org</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Trinity Episcopalian Church 
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
s a traditional church located right off campus on the corner of Chester and College. Its congregation is drawn from the Swarthmore community, including lots of families.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Jamie Birney ’10 (jbirney1)
<br />
<a href="www.trinityswarthmore.org">www.trinityswarthmore.org</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Renewal Presbyterian Church 
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is located in West Philly, and is largely attended by young Asian-Americans although it embraces all ethnicities. The services are contemporary with musical worship and a sermon.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Sara Kim ’10 (skim1) or Daniel Pak ’12 (dpak2)
<br />
<a href="www.renewalchurch.org">www.renewalchurch.org</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Circle of Hope 
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is a culturally progressive church located in South Philly with a young congregation. They meet Sunday evenings at 5pm and 7pm but also emphasizes meeting in small groups throughout the week.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Kristen Ridgeway (kristen.ridgeway@gmail) or Wes Willison ’12 (jwilli1)
<br />
<a href="www.circleofhope.net">www.circleofhope.net</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Swarthmore United Methodist Church 
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is located in the Swarthmore Ville next to the Swarthmore Public Library on Park Ave. Its congregation has members of different ages, single adults, and families.
<br />
<a href="www.sumcplace.com">www.sumcplace.com</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>


<tr>
<td class="subHeader">
Grace Covenant Church
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="bodyText">
is located on the University of Pennsylvania Campus. Its congregation is made up of mostly college students and young adults from nearby campuses.
<br />
<b>Contact:</b> Michio Taya '13 (mtaya1)
<br />
<a href="uc.gracecovenant.net">uc.gracecovenant.net</a>
<br /><br />
</td>
</tr>


</td>



